Bahrain Seeks Gulf States’ Help in Policing Protests, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-14T02:52:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/bahrain-seeks-gulf-states-help-in-policing-protests-ft-says.html
  Bahrain ’s Al Khalifa royal family
has asked the five other states in the Gulf Cooperation Council,
including  Saudi Arabia , for a security taskforce to help police
pro-democracy demonstrations after protesters fought Bahrain’s
riot police and occupied parts of the capital’s business
district yesterday, the Financial Times reported, citing people
familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 